# Routing rules

- Use `InvalidateRoute(reason)` after route-affecting changes.
- Do not allow unsafe cross-continent direct walk fallback.
- Direct flying is allowed only through `CW.CanUseCapabilityDirectFlyingLeg`.
- Parent/child map-layer transitions require explicit transport or marked parent fallback.
- Do not replace a child destination with parent silently. Mark fallback metadata.
- Known transports and learned transports must feed the graph through existing normalization/endpoint helpers.
- Single-node transports must keep zone/subzone aliases and may synthesize a from-side only through existing alias resolution.
- Flight Master/taxi transports are bidirectional and may be suppressed when direct flying mode makes them unnecessary.
- Keep query-node attachment cost-driven. Avoid hard pre-pruning that hides valid transport paths.
- `FindPathAStar` uses zero heuristic; treat it as uniform-cost search unless a proven admissible heuristic is introduced.
- Route output must preserve user label/name on queue stop points.

Subzone diagnostics:

- First inspect `/cw list` destination `maI`/mapName before changing graph logic.
- If queued destination is parent map, fix destination resolution or transport injection.
- If queued destination is child map and graph ends at parent, inspect explicit transport lookup/fallback continuation.
